api/!api/System.Security.Policy.Evidence.title: Evidence
api/!api/System.Security.Policy.Evidence.keywords: System Security Policy Evidence The Evidence class keeps track information that can used make security decisions about assembly AppDomain There are two types evidence one supplied the CLR host the other supplied the assembly itself keep dictionary that maps each type possbile evidence EvidenceTypeDescriptor which contains the evidence objects themselves they exist well some extra metadata about that type evidence This dictionary fully populated with keys for host evidence all times and for assembly evidence the first time the application evidence touched This means that Type key does not exist the dictionary then that particular type evidence will never given the assembly AppDomain question host evidence The only exception the user later manually adds host evidence via the AddHostEvidence API Assembly supplied evidence created front however host supplied evidence may lazily created the lazy creation case the Type will map either EvidenceTypeDescriptor that does not contain any evidence data null requests come for that evidence populate the EvidenceTypeDescriptor appropriately
